The 1938 diner was transformed in the mid-Eighties into Florent, one of those crazy late-night low-life / high-life cafes beloved of New Yorkers. Florent closed in 2008 and the premises now houses a branch of Madewell fashion outlets, though fortunately the historic aluminium ‘R&L Restaurant’ sign has been retained.
